  <prompt>
    Create the empty directory structure for the new `EmailComposer` module inside `@spaarke/ui-components`. This task lays the file-system contract Wave 1 fills in. NO implementation logic — just empty dirs + an `index.ts` placeholder that exports nothing yet + a commented-out barrel-export hookup in the shared library's top-level `src/index.ts`.

    The downstream tasks (011-029) will progressively uncomment the barrel lines as each piece lands. This keeps the build green at every intermediate step (no broken exports, no half-wired engine).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend developer familiar with `@spaarke/ui-components` shared library layout. Knows the convention: each component directory has a colocated `index.ts` that re-exports the public surface, and the lib's top-level `src/index.ts` aggregates the public surface from each component dir.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Empty `EmailComposer/` directory tree present under `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/`. Subdirs (`wrappers/`, `subcomponents/`, `modes/`, `__tests__/`) exist. `EmailComposer/index.ts` exists as an empty file with no exports. The shared lib top-level `src/index.ts` has a commented-out section reserving the EmailComposer barrel area. `npm run build` + `npm run lint` still pass (nothing broken).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
